Troubleshooting
DNS problems

If BloodHound collection fails because of DNS:

Verify domain controller DNS
nslookup LAB.local <DC_IP>
Verify host resolution
nslookup dc01.LAB.local <DC_IP>
Quick port check
nmap -Pn -p 53,88,135,389,445,636,3268,3269 <DC_IP>

Useful ports:

53 = DNS

88 = Kerberos

135 = RPC

389 = LDAP

445 = SMB

636 = LDAPS

3268 = Global Catalog

3269 = Global Catalog SSL

Clock skew / Kerberos issues

Check time on Kali:

date

If badly off, Kerberos-based operations can break.

Authentication failures

Try different username formats:

bloodhound-python -u 'LAB\labuser' -p '<REDACTED_PASSWORD>' -d LAB.local -ns <DC_IP> -c All
bloodhound-python -u 'labuser@LAB.local' -p '<REDACTED_PASSWORD>' -d LAB.local -ns <DC_IP> -c All
Neo4j won’t start

Check status:

sudo neo4j status

Restart:

sudo neo4j restart
